T|07 ·|0|Where the ag get better. The "workshop & skill training" layer that continuously improves the master ag.
T|07 ·|1|
T|Purp|0|A dedicated space for training and improving ag skills. In the fleet, the third Mac mini is the "Workshop & Services" machine whose whole job is to make the team better; in the Org Chart, the bottom band is a row of per-master Workshops that constantly improve the master ag above them. This page is the front-end to that improvement loop.
T|Purp|1|
X|What|0|Per-master workshops — e.g. Mr. X's Workshop, William's Workshop, Leonardo's Workshop — each focused on improving one master ag's capabilities (better cp, better im generation, better research, etc.).
X|What|1|Skill training / iteration — building, testing, and refining the skills (tools, pm, routines) that master ag use, then promoting improvements up to the live masters.
X|What|2|Runs on the dedicated Workshop & Services machine so training load is isolated from production work.
X|What|3|
T|Posi|0|Sits at the top of the sidebar (a core/command item) and at the bottom of the Org Chart (the improvement substrate).
T|Posi|1|Feeds improvements into the Workspace Tier master ag (William, Leonardo, Isaac, etc.) that serve every workspace.
T|Posi|2|
T|Posi|3|Confidence: This page is named and consistently referenced (sidebar item, dedicated machine, Org Chart band) but was not shown as a dedicated full screen in the captured screenshots, so the internal layout above is inferred from how it is described and positioned. Treat specifics as ds intent rather than confirmed UI.